oclcdcs.dc:creator: Minnesota News Council.
oclcdcs.dc:description: The few administrative records include minutes, financial records (especially fund raising materials), annual reports, and correspondence. Of particular interest are files (including audio and video tapes) documenting the council's public service announcements program.

The majority of the collection consists of mediation case files covering a wide range of complaints against the media including coverage of political matters, the abortion issue, municipal issues, and allegations of unfair media treatment by individuals and businesses.

Mediation case files (1971-1990) and various administrative records (1970-1992) documenting the activities of a council established in 1970 by the Minnesota Newspaper Association to mediate disputes between the media and the public. The council consists of twelve media representatives and twelve individual citizens.
oclcdcs.dc:relation: Finding aids: An inventory that provides additional information about this collection is available in the repository; filed in ALPHA notebooks under the heading: Minnesota News Council.
oclcdcs.dc:rights: Quotation or publication, beyond the fair use provisions of the copyright law, of anything in or based on the restricted records requires written permission.
Access to financial records less than ten years old requires written permission.
